PRESS DIGEST - Malaysia - June 2 . Following are the main stories in Monday ' s Malaysian newspapers . Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy . NEW STRAITS TIMES - - Acting Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim said he has summoned Rural Development Minister Annuar Musa for a meeting on Monday to discuss allegations that 600 million ringgit was missing from the Risda Replanting Fund . - - New Malacca chief minister Abu Zahar Isnin said the arrest of a state asemblyman on Saturday by Anti - Corruption Agency as indicating the government was serious in creating a clean , trustworthy image . - - Bank Islam has received shareholders ' approval over a proposal to restructure the company . - - Kuala Lumpur newsroom ( 603 - 201 4813 ) 
